<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,693,1067]" pageId="6" pageNumber="39">
Endemic to the Atlantic Forest (
<bibRefCitation author="Sobral, M. &amp; Lucas, E. &amp; Landrum, L. &amp; Soares-Silva, L." box="[545,768,732,758]" pageId="6" pageNumber="39" pagination="352 - 366" refId="ref15003" refString="Sobral, M., Lucas, E., Landrum, L. &amp; Soares-Silva, L. (2009) Myrtaceae. In: Stehmann, J., Forzza, R. C., Salino, A., Sobral, M., Costa, D. P. &amp; Kamino, L. H. Y. Plantas da Floresta Atlantica. Rio de Janeiro, pp 352 - 366." type="book chapter" year="2009">
Sobral 
<emphasis box="[636,697,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="39">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
) and known from the Northeastern (
<bibRefCitation author="Proenca, C. E. B. &amp; Sobral, M." pageId="6" pageNumber="39" pagination="111 - 113" refId="ref14537" refString="Proenca, C. E. B. &amp; Sobral, M. (2006) Myrtaceae, In: Barbosa, M. R. V., Sothers, C., Mayo, S., Gamarra-Rojas, C. F. L. &amp; Mesquita, A. C. (eds.). Checklist das Plantas do Nordeste Brasileiro: Angiospermas e Gymnospermas. Ministerio de Ciencia e Tecnologia, Brasilia, pp. 111 - 113." type="book chapter" year="2006">Proença &amp; Sobral 2006</bibRefCitation>
), Southeastern and Southern regions of 
<collectingCountry box="[700,773,770,796]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="39">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Govaerts, R. &amp; Sobral, M. &amp; Ashton, P. &amp; Barrie, F. &amp; Holst, B. K. &amp; Landrum, L. &amp; Matsumoto, K. &amp; Mazine, F. F. &amp; Lughadha, E. N. &amp; Proenca, C. &amp; Soares-Silva, L. H. &amp; Wilson, P. G. &amp; Lucas, E." box="[790,1043,770,796]" pageId="6" pageNumber="39" refId="ref13244" refString="Govaerts, R., Sobral, M., Ashton, P., Barrie, F., Holst, B. K., Landrum, L., Matsumoto, K., Mazine, F. F., Lughadha, E. N., Proenca, C., Soares-Silva, L. H., Wilson, P. G. &amp; Lucas, E. (2010) World Checklist of Myrtaceae. The Board of Trustees of the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew. Published on the Internet; http: // www. kew. org / wcsp /. Accessed: 29 July 2010." type="url" year="2010">
Govaerts 
<emphasis box="[909,970,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="39">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sobral, M. &amp; Proenca, C. &amp; Souza, M. &amp; Mazine, F. &amp; Lucas, E." box="[1056,1278,770,796]" pageId="6" pageNumber="39" refId="ref15080" refString="Sobral, M., Proenca, C., Souza, M., Mazine, F. &amp; Lucas, E. (2010) Myrtaceae. In: Forzza, R. C., Leitman, P. M., Costa, A. F., Carvalho Jr., A. A., Peixoto, A. L., Walter, B. M. T., Bicudo, C., Zappi, D., Costa, D. P., Lleras, E., Martinelli, G., Lima, H. C., Prado, J., Stehmann, J. R., Baumgratz, J. F. A., Pirani, J. R., Sylvestre, L., Maia, L. C., Lohmann, L. G., Queiroz, L. P., Silveira, M., Coelho, M. N., Mamede, M. C., Bastos, M. N. C., Morim, M. P., Barbosa, M. R., Menezes, M., Hopkins, M., Secco, R., Cavalcanti, T. B. &amp; Souza, V. C. Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro. Published on the internet; http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / 2010 / FB 010791. Accessed: 5 October 2011." type="url" year="2010">
Sobral 
<emphasis box="[1143,1204,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="39">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
). Considered extinct in the State of 
<collectingRegion box="[408,554,809,835]" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="6" pageNumber="39">Pernambuco</collectingRegion>
with no records collected in the last 50 years.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,693,1067]" pageId="6" pageNumber="39">
Trees 
<quantity box="[270,345,848,874]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="39" unit="m" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6 m</quantity>
tall, leaves 11–13 × 3.5–4.0 cm, midvein sulcate on adaxial lamina surface, raceme with the main axis reduced, apiculate bracts, lanceolate bracteoles, calyx closed in the flower bud and tearing irregularly, hypanthium and style glabrous, fruit globose.
</paragraph>
